%N A396275 Decimal expansion of the ratio of the inner radius to the outer radius of an annulus, such that the probability is 1/2 that a line segment connecting two points, chosen independently and uniformly at random in the annulus, lies entirely within it.
%C A396275 The real root of the equation (2*arccos(x) - 2*x*sqrt(1-x^2))/(1-x^2) = Pi/2.
%H A396275 Jonathan K. Hodge, Emily Marshall, and Geoff Patterson, <a href="https://www.jstor.org/stable/10.4169/074683410x510317">Gerrymandering and Convexity</a>, The College Mathematics Journal, Vol. 41, No. 4 (2010), pp. 312-324.
%H A396275 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/ConvexityCoefficient.html">Convexity Coefficient</a>.
%e A396275 0.527666247071849936578704812995867953584048771720152...
%t A396275 RealDigits[x /. FindRoot[(2*ArcCos[x] - 2*x*Sqrt[1 - x^2])/(1 - x^2) == Pi/2, {x, 1/2}, WorkingPrecision -> 120]][[1]]
%o A396275 (PARI) solve(x = 0.5, 0.6, (2*acos(x) - 2*x*sqrt(1-x^2))/(1-x^2) - Pi/2)
